<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11471&amp;p=131677#p131677</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11471&amp;p=131677#p131677"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Mode 7 help]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11471&amp;p=131677#p131677"><![CDATA[
<ul><li>Imagine a line of length 1 at the angle you want</li><li>&quot;sin theta&quot; is the sine of that value</li><li>&quot;cos theta&quot; is the cosine of that value</li><li>Multiply those two by the amount of scaling you want*</li></ul><br />Look up how sine and cosine work related to angles (in short: sine is the vertical distance, cosine is the horizontal distance). Also mind you, just use a look-up table with all the possible angles, the CPU is too weak to calculate it in real time.<br /><br />*Not sure, may be divide. Either way, you'd figure it out because if it's wrong it'll scale the other way.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4526">Sik</a> — Mon Jul 28, 2014 1:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
